  "texts": [
    "This imbalance leads to a biased model and degrades its performance.",
    "To mitigate the drawback, we propose an entropy-based regularization approach that steers the model output marginal probabilities to be more balanced.",
    "Experimental results in Section VI demonstrate the effectiveness of this technique.Before delving into details, we highlight the main contributions of this paper from four aspects:• We present an approach to build a new class of robust passive loss functions called Normalized Negative Loss Functions (NNLFs).",
    "By replacing the MAE in APL with our proposed NNLFs, we propose a new loss framework Active Negative Loss (ANL).• We analyze label imbalance in non-symmetric label noise scenarios and propose an entropy-based regularization technique to alleviate it.",
    "• We theoretically prove that our proposed NNLFs and ANL are robust to noisy labels and discuss the reason why replacing the MAE in APL with our NNLFs will improve performance in noisy label learning."
  ]
}